\"the form\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"a fittingly heroic defeat\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1168}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Somehow, though, the British duo reeled off a ridiculous seven points without reply to keep the flame burning bright, another chapter of Murrayian defiance writ, and the possibility still open that it might not be the last.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1192, \"end\": 1199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9948145047808558, \"rank\": 0.0031528941443998626, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ridiculous seven points\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"reply\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1272}, {\"ngram\": \"another chapter\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"Murrayian defiance writ\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1331}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's probably up there,\\\" Murray said, when asked where saving five match-points in a row ranked in a career punctuated by remarkable feats of escapology.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1550, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1422, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.877824107870026e-36, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"five match-points\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"a career\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1504}, {\"ngram\": \"remarkable feats\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"escapology\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The way that we were playing to that stage would have not suggested that we were likely to come back,\\\" he added in blunt terms.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1680, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The way\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1560}, {\"ngram\": \"that stage\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"blunt terms\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1679}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If Evans and Murray were unlikely victors until virtually the moment the deed was done, then at one stage earlier in the afternoon, as Evans lay sprawled on the Court 12 clay, banged up after an awkward fall during his opening match in the singles, they did not even appear certain participants.\", \"from\": 1682, \"to\": 1977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"score\": 0.9999999659344218, \"rank\": 3.4065783075661915e-08, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\"}, {\"begin\": 1695, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.877824107870026e-36, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"score\": 0.9999999659344218, \"rank\": 3.4065783075661915e-08, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"unlikely victors\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"virtually the moment\", \"from\": 1730, \"to\": 1750},