lling in a flash and then, with another break at the top of the second quickly consolidated, the end appeared nigh.\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 3134, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A 3-2 deficit\", \"from\": 2979, \"to\": 2992}, {\"ngram\": \"a 6-2 first set drilling\", \"from\": 3000, \"to\": 3024}, {\"ngram\": \"a flash\", \"from\": 3028, \"to\": 3035}, {\"ngram\": \"another break\", \"from\": 3051, \"to\": 3064}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3075}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3119}, {\"ngram\": \"nigh\", \"from\": 3129, \"to\": 3133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This being Murray, though, procession was somehow turned scrap.\", \"from\": 3136, \"to\": 3199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"procession\", \"from\": 3163, \"to\": 3173}, {\"ngram\": \"scrap\", \"from\": 3193, \"to\": 3198}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They levelled twice when threatening to be gapped, first to 2-2 in the second set and then 4-4.\", \"from\": 3200, \"to\": 3295, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the second set\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3281}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latter brought the most overt show of emotion from Murray, backed up by vigorous flapping of the growing number Union Jacks splattered among the vacant cream seats and chants that, in their accent, suggested one or two natives might have climbed on board.\", \"from\": 3296, \"to\": 3555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3351, \"end\": 3357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.877824107870026e-36, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 3412, \"end\": 3417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999186090504261, \"rank\": 8.139752621245884e-05, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\"